.TH "HTMLFORMELEMENT.RELLIST" "3JS" "November 25, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLFormElement.relList \- HTMLFormElement: relList property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]relList\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLFormElement\f[R] returns a live \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] object
containing the set of link types indicating the relationship between the
resource represented by the \f[CR]<form>\f[R] element and the current
document.
It reflects the \f[CR]<form>\f[R] element\(cqs \f[CR]rel\f[R] content
attribute.
.SH VALUE
A live \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] object.
.PP
Although the \f[CR]relList\f[R] property itself is read\-only in the
sense that you can\(cqt replace the \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] object, you
can still assign to the \f[CR]relList\f[R] property directly, which is
equivalent to assigning to its \f[CR]value\f[R] property.
You can also modify the \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] object using the
\f[CR]add()\f[R], \f[CR]remove()\f[R], \f[CR]replace()\f[R], and
\f[CR]toggle()\f[R] methods.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] form = document.querySelector(\(dqform\(dq);
form.relList.forEach((relEntry) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(relEntry);
});
.EE
